2017 New Zealand Election

Explanation

Click and drag to rotate the plot in three dimensions!

The columns are the same hexagons as in the flat hexmaps but the heights are the numbers of votes received.

Before you ask: the colours are randomly assigned (by default). I had a bit of trouble trying to get these working, and still haven’t figured out how to unsquash the hexagons or assign a uniform colour.

These views allow us to see a few things more clearly, such as how much higher the Green’s support is in Wellington, and the variation in support for the Māori Party among the Māori electorates.
